nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/george-daniel@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/george-daniel@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/george-daniel@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/george-daniel@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-1975">1975年</a>的<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/george-daniel">乔治·丹尼尔（George Daniel）</a>与奥斯卡·法雷尔（Oscar Farrell）合作制作了一张名为“ Volc3”的新单曲。在下面查看。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/the-1975-live-at-reading-review-setlist-photos-3489139">1975年在阅读节上：通过备受喜爱的首次亮相的光滑，安全，怀旧之旅</a></strong></li></ul><p>新曲目标志着DH2 Labelmates的第一个联合发行版，并逐渐建立为敲击的低音线。</p><p>它始于微妙而柔软的乐器，使歌曲闪烁着生命，因为它会发展动量并整合了环境样品和合成器，从而倾斜了焦点。</p><p>新曲目的到来也是在同一天（2月13日），该标签将首次将其臭名昭著的俱乐部之夜带到纽约的公共记录。它是<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-1975s-george-daniel-to-spearhead-dirty-hits-new-electronic-imprint-dh2-3766384">在伦敦举行的大型聚会之后，去年首次为自己取名的名字之后，以凯利·李·欧文斯（Kelly Lee Owens），泰勒·斯凯（Taylor Skye）和菩提（Bodhi）出场。</a></p><p>您可以<a href="https://ra.co/events/2075029" target="_blank" rel="noopener">在此处</a>找到有关纽约市公共记录的更多信息，并在下面查看乔治·丹尼尔（George Daniel）和奥斯卡·法雷尔（Oscar Farrell）的新曲目。 </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Volc3" width="696" height="522" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/EnlS7SFLyZ4?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p>丹尼尔（Daniel）和法雷尔（Farrell）之间的新合作是在前者大约在2024年DH2发布的同时发布自己的独奏材料。</p><p> Back at the end of July, the drummer, songwriter and producer <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-1975s-george-daniel-shares-debut-solo-single-screen-cleaner-3780333">launched his solo career with the debut single &#39;Screen Cleaner&#39;</a> , which officially marked his new venture into the electronic dance genre. It was shared on dh2, as it is <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-1975s-george-daniel-to-spearhead-dirty-hits-new-electronic-imprint-dh2-3766384">the electronic imprint he spearheads via The 1975&#39;s label, Dirty Hit</a> .</p><p> Since then, he shared another solo track in the form of &#39;Chlorine&#39;.</p><p> Speaking about his venture into solo material and exploration of the electronic genre, Daniel told <a href="https://theface.com/music/george-daniel-interview-charli-xcx-the-1975-new-label-dj-dh2-dirty-hit" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>The Face</em></a> that <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-1975s-george-daniel-says-he-doesnt-want-more-attention-in-going-solo-matty-can-have-everything-3781063">the move wasn&#39;t done in the hopes of bringing more attention to himself.</a></p><p> “I have a huge amount of imposter syndrome with this stuff – I think about this every day, like &#39;Oh, this is the guy who plays the drums and produces this band, they&#39;re successful, now he decides he&#39;s going to do a label because every other video on Instagram is a DJ right now&#39; – that&#39;s my nightmare,” he said last summer.</p><p> “The last thing I want people to think is like &#39;Oh, George wanted more attention.&#39;绝对不是。 Matty [Healy, 1975 frontman] can have everything!”</p><p> In the run up to the solo single, Daniel had been previewing his new material throughout the summer, including appearances with <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/glastonbury-2024-watch-charli-xcx-bring-out-robyn-and-romy-for-dancing-on-my-own-remix-during-dj-set-3770149">Charli at Glastonbury 2024</a> , Boiler Room New York, Ibiza&#39;s Amnesia and <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/jamie-xx-announces-10-night-london-club-residency-the-floor-3752401">The Floor with Jamie xx</a> at Venue MOT in London. </p><figure id="attachment_3817131" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3817131" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3817131" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/George-Daniel-and-Charli-XCX.-Credit_-David-M.-Benett_Jed-Cullen_Dave-Benett_Getty-Images.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/George-Daniel-and-Charli-XCX.-Credit_-David-M.-Benett_Jed-Cullen_Dave-Benett_Getty-Images.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/George-Daniel-and-Charli-XCX.-Credit_-David-M.-Benett_Jed-Cullen_Dave-Benett_Getty-Images-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/George-Daniel-and-Charli-XCX.-Credit_-David-M.-Benett_Jed-Cullen_Dave-Benett_Getty-Images-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/George-Daniel-and-Charli-XCX.-Credit_-David-M.-Benett_Jed-Cullen_Dave-Benett_Getty-Images-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/George-Daniel-and-Charli-XCX.-Credit_-David-M.-Benett_Jed-Cullen_Dave-Benett_Getty-Images-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/George-Daniel-and-Charli-XCX.-Credit_-David-M.-Benett_Jed-Cullen_Dave-Benett_Getty-Images-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3817131" class="wp-caption-text"> George Daniel and Charli XCX. CREDIT: David M. Benett/Jed Cullen/Dave Benett/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> The 1975 drummer co-produced <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-japanese-house">The Japanese House</a> &#39;s 2019 debut album <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/japanese-house-good-at-falling-review-2455260">&#39;Good At Falling&#39;</a> and its 2023 follow-up <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/the-japanese-house-in-the-end-it-always-does-review-3462887">&#39;In The End It Always Does&#39;</a> . Additionally, he has worked with the likes of <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/charli-xcx-and-the-1975s-george-daniel-remix-caroline-polacheks-welcome-to-my-island-3384402">Caroline Polachek</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/beabadoobee-to-share-new-track-with-the-1975s-matty-healy-and-george-daniel-this-week-2905415">Beabadoobee</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-radar/no-rome-interview-reading-the-1975-debut-album-dirty-hit-2541667">No Rome</a> .</p><p> For Oscar Farrell, the new track comes as he has been making a name for himself in the UK&#39;s electronic and dance music scene. He also recently released the single &#39;Running Free&#39;, which will be featured on his forthcoming debut EP &#39;I&#39;ve Already Called&#39;.</p><p> Set for release tomorrow (February 14), the EP is described in a release as reflecting the artist&#39;s “deep understanding of a variety of club-styles – taking in airy moments of two-step, grounding basslines and glitchy, chopped vocals.”</p><p> In other George Daniel news, as well as making waves with both his solo material and work with The 1975, he has also seen his work with fiancée <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/charli-xcx">Charli XCX</a> making its way onto the charts – collaborating with her on her hit album <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/charli-xcx-brat-review-lyrics-tracklist-3762875">&#39;Brat&#39;</a> .</p><p> He earned co-writing and production credits on the LP, and is credited on <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/charli-xcx-shares-two-new-singles-club-classics-and-b2b-3612821">&#39;Club Classics&#39;</a> – where Charli sings <em>“I wanna dance with George”</em> – and the viral hit <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/charli-xcx-says-viral-track-apple-nearly-didnt-make-the-cut-on-brat-3775668">&#39;Apple&#39;</a> .</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-1975-george-daniel-teams-up-with-oscar-farrell-for-euphoric-single-volc3-3837674">The 1975&#39;s George Daniel teams up with Oscar Farrell for euphoric single &#39;Volc3′</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>